title: Boys water polo: JSerra-Santa Margarita clash in key Trinity League game
text:
Â· posted by DAN ALBANO 
There is an important Trinity League boys water polo result to watch for today. 
JSerra plays host to Santa Margarita in a match that could determine at least third place and the final playoff berth from the Division 1 Trinity League. 
There are no at-large berths expected in the boys water polo playoffs. The game is scheduled for 4 p.m. at JSerra. The Lions opened league with a victory against Servite while the Eagles beat St. John Bosco. 
In an intriguing nonleague game, Villa Park plays at El Toro in a duel of county-ranked teams. 
Please send water polo news to Dan Albano at dalbano@ocregister.com More from Blog: OC Varsity
